        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 3:08PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 307 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Loveland, or 5 miles south of Fort Collins, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central Weld
and southeastern Larimer Counties, including the following locations:
New Windsor Reservoir and Kelim.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
